# MB Business – Security Policy Implementation

## 📜 Overview
This project involved implementing cybersecurity policies for a small-to-mid-sized business, focusing on risk management, compliance, and access control.

## 🛠️ Role & Tools
- Role: Policy Developer (Graduate Assignment)
- Tools: Microsoft Word, NIST 800-53, CIS Controls

## 🎯 Objective
To create realistic, enforceable cybersecurity policies for endpoint protection, employee access, and incident handling in a growing business.

## ✅ Key Deliverables
- Acceptable Use Policy (AUP)
- Access Control Policy (ACP)
- Endpoint Security Configuration Standards
- Incident Response Process

## 🧠 Lessons Learned
- Importance of aligning policy with both NIST and business goals
- Effective stakeholder communication
- How policy enforcement impacts real-world systems

